<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idef8c6689-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s101938"><num value="101938">§ 101938.</num><heading> Sunset</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The authority given to the Secretary under this subchapter shall expire 9 years after the date of the enactment of this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idef8c668a-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/114/289/tVII/s701">Pub. L. 114–289, title VII, § 701</ref>, <date date="2016-12-16">Dec. 16, 2016</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/130/1494">130 Stat. 1494</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/117/328/dG/tI/s123">Pub. L. 117–328, div. G, title I, § 123</ref>, <date date="2022-12-29">Dec. 29, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/4789">136 Stat. 4789</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idef8c668b-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idef8c668c-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idef8c668d-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The date of the enactment of this subchapter, referred to in text, is the date of enactment of <ref href="/us/pl/114/289">Pub. L. 114–289</ref>, which was approved <date date="2016-12-16">Dec. 16, 2016</date>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idef8c668e-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2022—<ref href="/us/pl/117/328">Pub. L. 117–328</ref> substituted “9” for “7”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
